1.10	2011_ATP_World_Tour_Finals_%E2%80%93_Singles	2011 ATP World Tour Finals – Singles	Roger Federer was the defending champion and confirmed the title, beating Jo-Wilfried Tsonga, 6–3, 6–7(6–8), 6–3 in the final. It was the 6th ATP World Tour Finals title for Federer and the 70th title of his whole career.	
